{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ALc6LEsDqH6QTNNwhFHS3W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even the 3.9 pods are crashing now. The issue is that the 3.12 version wrote something to the PVCs that 3.9 can't read back. This is because 3.12 may have initialized some state on disk that's incompatible with 3.9.\n\nWait, but that doesn't make sense since 3.12 was crashing immediately on boot with the `classic_mirrored_queue_version` error, so it shouldn't have written much. But the error in 3.9 now is also about feature flags...\n\nActually wait, looking at the error more carefully: `failed_to_initialize_feature_flags_registry`. \n\nNow I'm seeing the same error in 3.9 even though we rolled back the image. The pods are in `CrashLoopBackOff` with multiple restarts, which suggests something persisted on the PVCs when 3.12 briefly ran. Let me look at what 3.12 was actually complaining about—it seems to be related to a missing feature flag for `classic_mirrored_queue_version`.\n\nWait, I'm also noticing that only `rabbitmq-0` is showing in the pod list. Where are `rabbitmq-1` and `rabbitmq-2`? The StatefulSet was updated to 3.12 with `maxUnavailable=3`, which would have updated all three pods simultaneously, but then I rolled back to 3.9. The StatefulSet might be in an inconsistent state.\n\nLooking at the timestamps, `rabbitmq-0` is 10 minutes old and has restarted 6 times, which aligns with when we first upgraded to 3.12. But the other two pods should also be present if they were created during that update. They might not have been created yet, or something prevented them from coming up after the rollback. I'm realizing the rollout to 3.9 is stuck because rabbitmq-0 is crashing and won't become ready. Since the StatefulSet uses OrderedReady pod management, it needs rabbitmq-0 to be healthy before it can proceed to create or update the other pods—but with maxUnavailable=3, all three were terminated during the upgrade to 3.12, and now the controller is trying to bring them back one at a time starting with rabbitmq-0, which is failing.\n\nThe confusing part is that I'm seeing the same feature flag error from 3.12 in the 3.9 logs, which suggests either the rollback didn't actually take effect or the PVCs contain state that 3.9 can't handle. I need to verify what image is actually running and whether 3.12 left something in the persistent volumes that's preventing 3.9 from starting. I think I see what's happening now. When 3.12 starts up, it reads the existing feature flag state from the mnesia database that 3.9 created, then checks if all the required feature flags for 3.12 are enabled. Since `classic_mirrored_queue_version` is required in 3.12 but wasn't enabled in 3.9, the startup fails immediately during feature flag initialization.\n\nThe tricky part is what happens when 3.9 tries to roll back—if 3.12 partially wrote anything to the feature flag registry before crashing, 3.9 might encounter corrupted state. I need to look more carefully at the actual 3.9 error to see if it's the same failure or something different, and check what image is currently running in the pod to understand if it's actually been rotated to 3.12 yet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1004,"cache_read_input_tokens":43161,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1004},"output_tokens":15,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bafb32f9-6dcf-4dea-9467-b496907f09ca","uuid":"eebe0f2f-74f7-4e24-8f12-038eb46cb497","request_id":"req_011Cc13sgbpzVEUA2SxFhzv9"}
